title: Find Duplicates
description: Write a Python function that returns a list of duplicate elements from a given list.
constraints: Constraints: The input list will contain integers.
test:
def passTest():
	solution = Solution()
	param = [[1, 1, 2], [0, 3, 4, 2, 0, 2], [1, 1, 3, 4, 2, 1], [0, 0, 0], [1]]
	ans = [[1], [0, 2], [1], [0], []]
	for i in range(5):
		if ans[i] == solution.findDuplicates(param[i]):
			continue
		else
			return False
	return True
passedTest = 'Passed all test cases' if passTest() else 'Test cases failed'
print(passedTest)
